er\",\n        \"scan_events() — route handler\",\n        \"_compute_stats(inventory: dict) -> dict\",\n        \"inventory() — route handler\",\n        \"conflicts() — route handler\",\n        \"conflict_detail(filepath) — route handler\",\n        \"resolve() — route handler\",\n        \"resolve_all_latest() — route handler\",\n        \"execute() — route handler\",\n        \"merge_progress() — route handler\",\n        \"merge_events() — route handler\",\n        \"log_page() — route handler\",\n        \"export_log() — route handler\",\n        \"file_browser() — route handler\",\n        \"file_detail_api(filepath) — route handler\",\n        \"browse_tree_api() — route handler\",\n        \"resolve_accept_defaults() — route handler\",\n        \"resolve_toggle() — route handler\",\n        \"file_content(filepath) — route handler\",\n        \"merge_editor(filepath) — route handler\",\n        \"save_merge() — route handler\",\n        \"coverage_page() — route handler\",\n        \"coverage_api() — route handler\",\n        \"coverage_files_api(source_name) — route handler\"\n      ],\n      \"imports_from\": [\n        \"os — standard library\",\n        \"sys — standard library\",\n        \"hashlib — standard library\",\n        \"json — standard library\",\n        \"difflib — standard library\",\n        \"threading — standard library\",\n        \"fnmatch — standard library\",\n        \"shutil — standard library\",\n        \"time — standard library\",\n        \"queue — standard library\",\n        \"re — standard library\",\n        \"sqlite3 — standard library\",\n        \"datetime.datetime — standard library\",\n        \"pathlib.Path — standard library\",\n        \"dataclasses.dataclass, field, asdict — standard library\",\n        \"typing.Optional — standard library\",\n        \"urllib.parse.unquote — standard library\",\n        \"concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor, as_completed — standard library\",\n        \"flask.Flask, render_template, request, redirect, url_for, jsonify, Response, stream_with_context, flash — external (Flask)\",\n        \"markupsafe.Markup — external (MarkupSafe)\"\n      ],\n      \"key_functions\": [\n        \"FileScanner.build_inventory(sources: list) -> dict — scans all sources and builds merged inventory with categorization\",\n        \"FileScanner.scan_source(source: SourceConfig) -> dict — scans a single source directory with auto-detection of editor history format\",\n        \"FileScanner._scan_editor_history_source(source, project_filter) -> dict — parses Windsurf/VS Code/Cursor history directories\",\n        \"FileScanner._categorize(item: MergeItem) — categorizes files as auto_unique, auto_identical, or conflict\",\n        \"MergeEngine.execute_merge(inventory, target_dir, progress_queue) — executes file copy operations with progress reporting\",\n        \"MergeEngine.generate_diff(version_a, version_b) -> list — generates unified diff between two file versions\",\n        \"EditorHistoryExtractor.extract_all(dest_dir, project_filter, hours) -> dict — extracts files from editor history to destination\",\n        \"save_inventory_state(inventory) — bulk-saves inventory to SQLite\",\n        \"load_inventory_state(session_id) — loads inventory from SQLite with JSON fallback\",\n        \"setup() — Flask route handling source configuration and scan initiation\",\n        \"conflict_detail(filepath) — Flask route for conflict resolution UI\",\n        \"merge_editor(filepath) — Flask route for interactive merge editor\",\n        \"save_merge() — API endpoint for saving manually merged files\"\n      ],\n      \"patterns\": [\n        \"Monolithic architecture — entire application in single file\",\n        \"MVC pattern — Flask routes (controllers), Jinja2 templates (views), dataclasses (models)\",\n        \"Repository pattern — SQLite persistence layer with session management\",\n        \"Thread pool concurrency — ThreadPoolExecutor for parallel file scanning\",\n        \"Producer-consumer pattern — queue.Queue for progress reporting between threads\",\n        \"Server-Sent Events (SSE) — real-time progress streaming via /scan-events, /merge-events, /extract-events\",\n        \"Dataclass models — FileVersion, MergeItem, SourceConfig as immutable data structures\",\n        \"State management — global state dictionary with session persistence\",\n        \"Auto-detection strategy — FileScanner automatically detects editor history vs regular directories\",\n        \"Three-method fallback — EditorHistoryExtractor tries multiple strategies to locate backup files\"\n      ],\n      \"summary\": \"A monolithic Flask web application for multi-source file recovery and merging, featuring FileScanner for directory scanning with editor history auto-detection, MergeEngine for conflict resolution and file operations, EditorHistoryExtractor for Windsurf/VS Code/Cursor history parsing, SQLite-based session persistence, and comprehensive Flask routes for setup wizard, file browser, inventory management, conflict resolution, merge editor, and coverage dashboard.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"area_summary\": \"The core-application area is a single-file monolithic Flask web application (file_merger.py) that provides a complete file recovery and merging system. It follows an MVC architectural pattern with dataclass models (FileVersion, MergeItem, SourceConfig), service classes (FileScanner, MergeEngine, EditorHistoryExtractor, RecoveryAdvisor), and Flask route controllers. The application uses SQLite for session persistence with WAL mode for concurrent access, thread pools for parallel scanning, and Server-Sent Events for real-time progress updates. Key abstractions include the FileScanner which auto-detects and parses editor history formats (Windsurf, VS Code, Cursor) alongside regular directories, and the MergeEngine which categorizes files as unique, identical, or conflicting and executes merge operations with comprehensive logging.\",\n  \"cross_area_refs\": [\n    \"imports render_template from web-templates (Jinja2 templates: setup.html, scan_progress.html, inventory.html, conflicts.html, conflict_detail.html, merge_progress.html, log.html, browse.html, _file_detail.html, merge_editor.html, coverage.html, extract_history.html, extract_progress.html)\",\n    \"references EditorHistoryExtractor.EDITOR_HISTORY_PATHS which accesses Windsurf/VS Code/Cursor history directories outside the project\",\n    \"writes session data to local filesystem at SESSIONS_DIR (./sessions/)\",\n    \"writes merge logs to local filesystem as merge_log_*.json files\"\n  ],\n  \"suggested_splits\": [\n    {\n      \"suggestion\": \"Split into modular package structure\",\n      \"rationale\": \"The file is 2,861 lines and contains multiple distinct domains that could be separated: models (FileVersion, MergeItem, SourceConfig), services (FileScanner, MergeEngine, EditorHistoryExtractor, RecoveryAdvisor), persistence (SQLite session management), and web layer (Flask routes). Consider splitting into: models.py, scanner.py, merge_engine.py, history_extractor.py, persistence.py, and routes/ directory with route modules.\",\n      \"priority\": \"medium\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"suggestion\": \"Extract EditorHistoryExtractor to standalone module\",\n      \"rationale\": \"The EditorHistoryExtractor class (240+ lines) is a distinct domain dealing with editor-specific history parsing. It could be moved to a separate history_extractor.py module for better maintainability and to allow reuse by the standalone PowerShell recovery script.\",\n      \"priority\": \"low\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```",
