    "role": "user",
    "content": "## Your Area Assignment\n\n**Area:** agentic-knowledge\n**Description:** Agentic system documentation, workflow definitions, and skill examples. Rules docs cover architecture overview, JSON definitions, knowledge system, skills format, and workflow execution model.\n**File patterns:** [\"agentic/rules/docs/*.md\", \"agentic/skills/example-skill/SKILL.md\", \"agentic/workflows/example_workflow.json\"]\n\n## Plan Summary\n\nAreas in the plan:\n- core-application: The monolithic Flask web application for multi-source file recovery and merging. Contains FileScanner, MergeEngine, EditorHistoryExtractor, SQLite session persistence, and all Flask routes in a single file.\n- web-templates: Jinja2 HTML templates for the Flask web UI: setup wizard, file browser, inventory, conflict resolution, merge editor, coverage dashboard, and SSE progress pages. All use Bootstrap 5 dark theme.\n- agentic-engine: Core agentic engine package: OpenRouter API client, workflow runner with multi-layer execution, ReAct-style agentic loop (text and native tool-calling modes), tool executor with safe dispatch, and knowledge/skills resolver.\n- agentic-tools: Tool implementations for the agentic engine: file tree walker, directory lister, file reader, code searcher, and file writer. Includes JSON tool definitions schema.\n- agentic-knowledge: Agentic system documentation, workflow definitions, and skill examples. Rules docs cover architecture overview, JSON definitions, knowledge system, skills format, and workflow execution model.\n- claude-config-and-rules: Claude Code configuration: global rules index, coding rules (invariants, testing, bug-fixing), skills (code-documenter, code-search), spark configuration, plans, and test infrastructure.\n- project-root-files: Top-level project files: CLAUDE.md project overview, PowerShell recovery script for standalone editor history extraction, commands reference, and version marker.\n\n## Instructions\n\nAnalyze all files matching your area's patterns. Return a JSON report with `area`, `files`, `area_summary`, `cross_area_refs`, and optionally `suggested_splits`."
