{
  "content": " **Objective**\nAnalyze the `web-templates` area (Jinja2 HTML templates for a Flask file recovery/merger application) and produce a structured JSON report covering template roles, dependencies, and architectural patterns.\n\n**Actions taken**\n- Listed `templates/` directory (14 files identified)\n- Read and analyzed all templates:\n  - **base.html**: Bootstrap 5 dark theme layout foundation with blocks for title, CSS, content, JS\n  - **setup.html**: Configuration wizard with dynamic source directory inputs and session management\n  - **browse.html**: Interactive file tree with AJAX loading, recursive rendering, keyboard navigation, real-time filtering\n  - **inventory.html**: Statistics dashboard with filtering/sorting controls\n  - **conflicts.html**: Conflict list view with progress tracking and bulk resolution actions\n  - **conflict_detail.html**: Side-by-side version comparison with selection cards\n  - **merge_editor.html**: Hunk-based merge editor with pick/choose functionality for conflicting sections\n  - **coverage.html**: Source coverage visualization with segmented progress bars\n  - **extract_history.html**: Editor history extraction setup (VS Code/Windsurf/Cursor)\n  - **extract_progress.html**, **scan_progress.html**, **merge_progress.html**: SSE (Server-Sent Events) progress pages with real-time status updates\n  - **log.html**: Merge results viewer with statistics cards\n  - **_file_detail.html**: AJAX-loaded file detail panel for browse view\n\n**Result**\nGenerated JSON report containing:\n- Template file paths and roles\n- Exported blocks and components\n- Cross-area imports from `core-application` (Flask routes/API endpoints)\n- Key JavaScript functions (e.g., `loadTree()`, `pickVer()`, `navHunk()`)\n- UI patterns (AJAX loading, recursive trees, SSE, keyboard shortcuts)\n- Summaries of each template's purpose\n\n**Artefacts**\n- **No files created/modified** (read-only analysis)\n- **Output**: Structured JSON report (partially sh