  {
    "role": "tool",
    "tool_call_id": "functions.search_code:77",
    "content": "{\"matches\": [{\"file\": \".gitignore\", \"line\": 1, \"content\": \"sessions/\"}, {\"file\": \".gitignore\", \"line\": 2, \"content\": \".merger_config.json\"}, {\"file\": \".gitignore\", \"line\": 3, \"content\": \".merger_state.json\"}, {\"file\": \".gitignore\", \"line\": 4, \"content\": \"merge_log_*.json\"}, {\"file\": \".gitignore\", \"line\": 5, \"content\": \"__pycache__/\"}, {\"file\": \".gitignore\", \"line\": 6, \"content\": \"*.pyc\"}, {\"file\": \"0.12.0\", \"line\": 1, \"content\": \"Requirement already satisfied: pathspec in .\\\\.venv\\\\Lib\\\\site-packages (1.0.4)\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 1, \"content\": \"# CLAUDE.md \\u2014 Guanine (CodeEdit)\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 2, \"content\": \"\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 3, \"content\": \"## Project Overview\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 4, \"content\": \"\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 5, \"content\": \"**Guanine (CodeEdit)** \\u2014 A multi-source file recovery and merge tool with a Flask web UI. Scans directories and editor local history (Windsurf, VS Code, Cursor), identifies conflicts between file versions across multiple sources, and lets you review side-by-side diffs and merge into a target directory. Includes a companion PowerShell script for standalone history extraction.\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 6, \"content\": \"\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 7, \"content\": \"Stack: Python, Flask, SQLite, Jinja2, Bootstrap 5, pytest\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 8, \"content\": \"\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 9, \"content\": \"## Rule and Skill Discovery Protocol\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 10, \"content\": \"\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 11, \"content\": \"Do NOT expect a full list of rules or skills in this file.\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 12, \"content\": \"The project uses a decentralised documentation system. Follow this protocol:\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 13, \"content\": \"\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 14, \"content\": \"### Before starting any task:\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 15, \"content\": \"\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 16, \"content\": \"1. **Identify affected modules.** Look at the file paths involved in the task.\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 17, \"content\": \"   Map each path to its module or app.\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 18, \"content\": \"\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 19, \"content\": \"2. **Read the module's index.** For each affected module, read:\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 20, \"content\": \"   ```\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 21, \"content\": \"   <module-path>/.claude/RULES_INDEX.md\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 22, \"content\": \"   ```\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 23, \"content\": \"   This lists all documentation rules, coding rules, and skills\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 24, \"content\": \"   available for that module with one-line summaries.\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 25, \"content\": \"\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 26, \"content\": \"3. **Load relevant rules only.** Based on the index and the specific\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 27, \"content\": \"   files you are editing, read only the rules that apply.\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 28, \"content\": \"   Do NOT load rules for unrelated modules or files.\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 29, \"content\": \"\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 30, \"content\": \"4. **Check global rules.** Always check these locations for project-wide\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 31, \"content\": \"   rules that apply regardless of module:\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 32, \"content\": \"   ```\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 33, \"content\": \"   .claude/RULES_INDEX.md           (global rules index)\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 34, \"content\": \"   .claude/rules/                   (global coding rules)\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 35, \"content\": \"   .claude/rules/invariants.md      (design invariants \\u2014 MUST NOT be violated)\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 36, \"content\": \"   ```\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 37, \"content\": \"\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 38, \"content\": \"### For cross-module tasks:\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 39, \"content\": \"\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 40, \"content\": \"If a task spans multiple modules, read the RULES_INDEX.md for ALL affected\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 41, \"content\": \"modules and load rules from each that are relevant.\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 42, \"content\": \"\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 43, \"content\": \"### After completing code changes:\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 44, \"content\": \"\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 45, \"content\": \"If you created or significantly modified a file, check if a documentation\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 46, \"content\": \"rule exists for it. If one exists and may be stale, ask: \\\"Should I update\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 47, \"content\": \"the documentation rule for this file?\\\" If the user agrees, use the\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 48, \"content\": \"`code-documenter` skill.\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 49, \"content\": \"\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 50, \"content\": \"## Architecture\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 51, \"content\": \"\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 52, \"content\": \"- **File Scanner** (`file_merger.py` \\u2014 `FileScanner` class) \\u2014 Walks source directories, computes SHA-256 hashes, detects binary files, categorizes items as unique/identical/conflict\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 53, \"content\": \"- **Merge Engine** (`file_merger.py` \\u2014 `MergeEngine` class) \\u2014 Generates unified and side-by-side diffs, executes file copy/merge operations with skip-if-identical logic\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 54, \"content\": \"- **Editor History Extractor** (`file_merger.py` \\u2014 `EditorHistoryExtractor` class) \\u2014 Parses Windsurf/VS Code/Cursor local history directories (`entries.json`), resolves hashed backup files to original paths\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 55, \"content\": \"- **Session Persistence** (`file_merger.py` \\u2014 SQLite layer) \\u2014 Stores scan results, merge items, file versions, and coverage stats in per-session SQLite databases with WAL mode\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 56, \"content\": \"- **Flask Web UI** (`file_merger.py` \\u2014 Flask routes + `templates/`) \\u2014 Setup wizard, scan progress (SSE), inventory browser, conflict resolution, interactive merge editor, coverage dashboard\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 57, \"content\": \"- **PowerShell Recovery Script** (`restore_deleted_files.ps1`) \\u2014 Standalone script for finding and restoring files from editor history without the web UI\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 58, \"content\": \"- **HTML Templates** (`templates/`) \\u2014 14 Jinja2 templates: setup, browse, inventory, conflicts, conflict detail, merge editor, coverage, extraction, progress pages\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 59, \"content\": \"\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 60, \"content\": \"## Directory Layout\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 61, \"content\": \"\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 62, \"content\": \"```\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 63, \"content\": \"Guanine(CodeEdit)/\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 64, \"content\": \"\\u251c\\u2500\\u2500 CLAUDE.md                              <- You are here\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 65, \"content\": \"\\u251c\\u2500\\u2500 .claude/\"}, {\"file\": \"CLAUDE.md\", \"line\": 66, \"content\": \"\\u250