    "role": "user",
    "content": "## Explorer Area Summaries\n\n\n### Area: claude-config-and-rules\n\n**Summary:** \n\n**Cross-area references:** []\n\n**Files:**\n\n\n### Area: agentic-tools\n\n**Summary:** The agentic-tools area provides a suite of filesystem and code exploration utilities for the agentic engine. All tools follow a consistent pattern: they accept a `_base_dir` parameter for sandboxing, validate paths to prevent directory traversal attacks, and return JSON-encoded responses with either success data or error messages. The tools support read/write operations, directory listing (flat and recursive), file tree generation, and regex-based code search with configurable filters. The definitions.json file serves as the contract between the tool implementations and the agentic engine's tool executor, defining parameter schemas and logical tool groupings.\n\n**Cross-area references:** [\"agentic.tools.read_file.execute referenced in definitions.json\", \"agentic.tools.write_file.execute referenced in definitions.json\", \"agentic.tools.list_directory.execute referenced in definitions.json\", \"agentic.tools.search_code.execute referenced in definitions.json\", \"agentic.tools.get_file_tree.execute referenced in definitions.json\"]\n\n**Files:**\n  - **agentic/tools/__init__.py** (entry-point): Package initialization file with module docstring declaring this as tool implementations for the agentic engine.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n  - **agentic/tools/definitions.json** (config): JSON schema defining 5 tools (read_file, write_file, list_directory, search_code, get_file_tree) with their parameter schemas and logical groupings into code_analysis and file_ops tool sets.\n    Exports: [\"tools (array of tool definitions)\", \"tool_sets (groupings: code_analysis, file_ops)\"]\n    Imports from: []\n  - **agentic/tools/get_file_tree.py** (utility): Generates an indented text representation of the directory tree, respecting skip lists for common directories and binary extensions, with configurable depth and hidden file inclusion.\n    Exports: [\"execute(max_depth=4, include_hidden=False, _base_dir='.', **kwargs) -> str\"]\n    Imports from: [\"json (standard library)\", \"os (standard library)\", \"pathlib.Path (standard library)\"]\n  - **agentic/tools/list_directory.py** (utility): Lists files and directories at a given path with optional recursive listing up to depth 3, including path validation to prevent directory escape.\n    Exports: [\"execute(path='.', recursive=False, _base_dir='.', **kwargs) -> str\"]\n    Imports from: [\"json (standard library)\", \"os (standard library)\"]\n  - **agentic/tools/read_file.py** (utility): Reads file contents with optional line range selection, converting 1-based line numbers to 0-based for slicing, with path validation.\n    Exports: [\"execute(path, start_line=None, end_line=None, _base_dir='.', **kwargs) -> str\"]\n    Imports from: [\"json (standard library)\", \"os (standard library)\"]\n  - **agentic/tools/search_code.py** (utility): Performs regex pattern search across files with optional file glob filtering, skipping common directories and binary extensions, with match limiting and truncation reporting.\n    Exports: [\"execute(pattern, file_pattern=None, path='.', _base_dir='.', **kwargs) -> str\"]\n    Imports from: [\"fnmatch (standard library)\", \"json (standard library)\", \"os (standard library)\", \"re (standard library)\"]\n  - **agentic/tools/write_file.py** (utility): Writes content to a file, automatically creating parent directories, with path validation and line count reporting in the response.\n    Exports: [\"execute(path, content, _base_dir='.', **kwargs) -> str\"]\n    Imports from: [\"json (standard library)\", \"os (standard library)\"]\n\n### Area: agentic-engine\n\n**Summary:** The agentic-engine area provides a complete, framework-agnostic autonomous agent execution platform. It follows a layered architecture with clear separation: OpenRouterClient handles external LLM communication with retry logic; LightweightWorkflowSession maintains execution state across multi-layer workflows; the runner orchestrates layer dispatch (prompt, agentic_loop, smart_template, tool); loop.py implements dual-mode agentic reasoning (ReAct text-parsing and native tool-calling); tool_executor provides safe dispatch and defensive JSON parsing; and knowledge.py manages prompt assembly from markdown rules and skills. The design emphasizes stdlib-only dependencies (except Jinja2), safe execution with signature filtering, and flexible workflow definitions via JSON.\n\n**Cross-area references:** [\"imports jinja2 from external package (runner.py)\", \"references agentic.tools module in README.md examples\", \"references agentic/workflows/ directory in README.md\", \"references agentic/skills/ directory in knowledge.py discover_skills()\", \"references agentic/skill_definitions/ directory in knowledge.py discover_skills()\", \"references rules/docs/ directory in README.md documentation links\"]\n\n**Files:**\n  - **agentic/engine/__init__.py** (entry-point): Package entry point that exports all public APIs from the agentic engine submodules, serving as the unified interface for workflow execution, agentic loops, tool execution, and knowledge resolution.\n    Exports: [\"OpenRouterClient\", \"LightweightWorkflowSession\", \"process_layer(layer_def, session, client, tool_registry) -> dict\", \"run_workflow(workflow_json, client, tool_registry, input_data) -> dict\", \"execute_tool_call(available_tools, tool_name, tool_args) -> str\", \"extract_json(response) -> dict | None\", \"parse_tool_args(raw_args) -> dict\", \"process_agentic_loop(layer_def, session, client, tool_registry, knowledge) -> dict\", \"process_agentic_loop_native(layer_def, session, client, tool_registry, knowledge) -> dict\", \"summarize_loop(chat_history, client, model) -> str\", \"extract_frontmatter(file_path) -> dict\", \"resolve_knowledge(rules, skills, knowledge_set, base_dir) -> dict\", \"build_rules_index(file_paths) -> str\", \"build_skills_index(metadata) -> str\", \"discover_skills(base_dir) -> list[dict]\"]\n    Imports from: [\"OpenRouterClient from .openrouter\", \"LightweightWorkflowSession, process_layer, run_workflow from .runner\", \"execute_tool_call, extract_json, parse_tool_args from .tool_executor\", \"process_agentic_loop, process_agentic_loop_native, summarize_loop from .loop\", \"extract_frontmatter, resolve_knowledge, build_rules_index, build_skills_index, discover_skills from .knowledge\"]\n  - **agentic/engine/openrouter.py** (service): Lightweight stdlib-only HTTP client for the OpenRouter API providing chat completions with automatic retry, exponential backoff, and normalized response handling.\n    Exports: [\"OpenRouterClient(api_key, base_url) -> OpenRouterClient\", \"OpenRouterClient.chat_completion(model, messages, tools, max_tokens, temperature, stop) -> dict\", \"OpenRouterError(message, status_code) -> OpenRouterError\"]\n    Imports from: [\"json (stdlib)\", \"logging (stdlib)\", \"time (stdlib)\", \"urllib.error (stdlib)\", \"urllib.request (stdlib)\", \"typing.Any\"]\n  - **agentic/engine/runner.py** (controller): Workflow runner orchestrating multi-layer workflow execution with session state management, Jinja2 templating, and layer dispatch for prompts, agentic loops, templates, and direct tool calls.\n    Exports: [\"LightweightWorkflowSession() -> LightweightWorkflowSession\", \"LightweightWorkflowSession.add_input(obj) -> None\", \"LightweightWorkflowSession.get_input() -> dict\", \"LightweightWorkflowSession.log_output(**kwargs) -> None\", \"LightweightWorkflowSession.get_current_layer() -> int\", \"LightweightWorkflowSession.to_dict() -> dict\", \"process_layer(layer_def, session, client, tool_registry) -> dict\", \"run_workflow(workflow_json, client, tool_registry, input_data) -> dict\"]\n    Imports from: [\"copy (stdlib)\", \"json (stdlib)\", \"logging (stdlib)\", \"re (stdlib)\", \"typing.Any\", \"jinja2 (external)\", \"OpenRouterClient from .openrouter\", \"process_agentic_loop, process_agentic_loop_native from .loop\", \"resolve_knowledge from .knowledge\", \"execute_tool_call from .tool_executor\"]\n  - **agentic/engine/loop.py** (controller): Dual-mode agentic loop implementation supporting both ReAct text-parsing and native OpenAI-format tool calling, with shared system message assembly and automatic conversation summarization.\n    Exports: [\"process_agentic_loop(layer_def, session, client, tool_registry, knowledge) -> dict\", \"process_agentic_loop_native(layer_def, session, client, tool_registry, knowledge) -> dict\", \"summarize_loop(chat_history, client, model) -> str\"]\n    Imports from: [\"json (stdlib)\", \"logging (stdlib)\", \"re (stdlib)\", \"typing.Any\", \"execute_tool_call from .tool_executor\"]\n  - **agentic/engine/tool_executor.py** (service): Tool execution utilities handling JSON extraction from LLM outputs with multiple fallback strategies and safe tool dispatch with signature-aware argument filtering.\n    Exports: [\"extract_json(response) -> dict | None\", \"parse_tool_args(raw_args) -> dict\", \"execute_tool_call(available_tools, tool_name, tool_args) -> str\"]\n    Imports from: [\"inspect (stdlib)\", \"json (stdlib)\", \"logging (stdlib)\", \"re (stdlib)\", \"typing.Any\"]\n  - **agentic/engine/knowledge.py** (service): Knowledge resolution system for assembling rules, skills, and documentation into agent prompts with frontmatter extraction, skill discovery, and index generation.\n    Exports: [\"extract_frontmatter(file_path) -> dict\", \"build_rules_index(file_paths) -> str\", \"build_skills_index(metadata) -> str\", \"discover_skills(base_dir) -> list[dict]\", \"resolve_knowledge(rules, skills, knowledge_set, base_dir) -> dict\"]\n    Imports from: [\"json (stdlib)\", \"logging (stdlib)\", \"os (stdlib)\", \"re (stdlib)\", \"pathlib.Path\", \"typing.Any\"]\n  - **agentic/README.md** (documentation): Comprehensive documentation for the agentic engine covering workflow definition, tool creation, skill authoring, and quick-start examples.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n\n### Area: core-application\n\n**Summary:** The core-application area is a single-file monolithic Flask web application (file_merger.py) that provides a complete file recovery and merging system. It follows an MVC architectural pattern with dataclass models (FileVersion, MergeItem, SourceConfig), service classes (FileScanner, MergeEngine, EditorHistoryExtractor, RecoveryAdvisor), and Flask route controllers. The application uses SQLite for session persistence with WAL mode for concurrent access, thread pools for parallel scanning, and Server-Sent Events for real-time progress updates. Key abstractions include the FileScanner which auto-detects and parses editor history formats (Windsurf, VS Code, Cursor) alongside regular directories, and the MergeEngine which categorizes files as unique, identical, or conflicting and executes merge operations with comprehensive logging.\n\n**Cross-area references:** [\"imports render_template from web-templates (Jinja2 templates: setup.html, scan_progress.html, inventory.html, conflicts.html, conflict_detail.html, merge_progress.html, log.html, browse.html, _file_detail.html, merge_editor.html, coverage.html, extract_history.html, extract_progress.html)\", \"references EditorHistoryExtractor.EDITOR_HISTORY_PATHS which accesses Windsurf/VS Code/Cursor history directories outside the project\", \"writes session data to local filesystem at SESSIONS_DIR (./sessions/)\", \"writes merge logs to local filesystem as merge_log_*.json files\"]\n\n**Files:**\n  - **file_merger.py** (entry-point): A monolithic Flask web application for multi-source file recovery and merging, featuring FileScanner for directory scanning with editor history auto-detection, MergeEngine for conflict resolution and file operations, EditorHistoryExtractor for Windsurf/VS Code/Cursor history parsing, SQLite-based session persistence, and comprehensive Flask routes for setup wizard, file browser, inventory management, conflict resolution, merge editor, and coverage dashboard.\n    Exports: [\"FileVersion \\u2014 dataclass representing a scanned file version with metadata\", \"MergeItem \\u2014 dataclass representing a file with multiple versions from different sources\", \"SourceConfig \\u2014 dataclass for source directory configuration\", \"FileScanner \\u2014 class for scanning directories and building file inventory\", \"MergeEngine \\u2014 class for executing merges and generating diffs\", \"RecoveryAdvisor \\u2014 class providing recovery suggestions\", \"EditorHistoryExtractor \\u2014 class for extracting files from editor history\", \"generate_side_by_side_diff(version_a, version_b, context_lines=3) -> list\", \"SESSIONS_DIR \\u2014 constant for session storage path\", \"list_sessions() -> list\", \"get_active_session_id() -> str\", \"set_active_session(session_id: str)\", \"save_session_meta(session_id: str, session_name: str = '')\", \"save_config(sources, target_dir, ignore_patterns)\", \"load_config(session_id: str = '') -> dict\", \"save_inventory_state(inventory)\", \"save_item_resolution(relative_path: str, selected_index: int, resolved: bool)\", \"save_batch_resolutions(updates: list)\", \"load_inventory_state(session_id: str = '')\", \"delete_session(session_id: str)\", \"app \\u2014 Flask application instance\", \"index() \\u2014 route handler\", \"switch_session(session_id) \\u2014 route handler\", \"new_session() \\u2014 route handler\", \"delete_session_route(session_id) \\u2014 route handler\", \"extract_history() \\u2014 route handler\", \"extract_progress() \\u2014 route handler\", \"extract_events() \\u2014 route handler\", \"setup() \\u2014 route handler\", \"scan_progress() \\u2014 route handler\", \"scan_events() \\u2014 route handler\", \"_compute_stats(inventory: dict) -> dict\", \"inventory() \\u2014 route handler\", \"conflicts() \\u2014 route handler\", \"conflict_detail(filepath) \\u2014 route handler\", \"resolve() \\u2014 route handler\", \"resolve_all_latest() \\u2014 route handler\", \"execute() \\u2014 route handler\", \"merge_progress() \\u2014 route handler\", \"merge_events() \\u2014 route handler\", \"log_page() \\u2014 route handler\", \"export_log() \\u2014 route handler\", \"file_browser() \\u2014 route handler\", \"file_detail_api(filepath) \\u2014 route handler\", \"browse_tree_api() \\u2014 route handler\", \"resolve_accept_defaults() \\u2014 route handler\", \"resolve_toggle() \\u2014 route handler\", \"file_content(filepath) \\u2014 route handler\", \"merge_editor(filepath) \\u2014 route handler\", \"save_merge() \\u2014 route handler\", \"coverage_page() \\u2014 route handler\", \"coverage_api() \\u2014 route handler\", \"coverage_files_api(source_name) \\u2014 route handler\"]\n    Imports from: [\"os \\u2014 standard library\", \"sys \\u2014 standard library\", \"hashlib \\u2014 standard library\", \"json \\u2014 standard library\", \"difflib \\u2014 standard library\", \"threading \\u2014 standard library\", \"fnmatch \\u2014 standard library\", \"shutil \\u2014 standard library\", \"time \\u2014 standard library\", \"queue \\u2014 standard library\", \"re \\u2014 standard library\", \"sqlite3 \\u2014 standard library\", \"datetime.datetime \\u2014 standard library\", \"pathlib.Path \\u2014 standard library\", \"dataclasses.dataclass, field, asdict \\u2014 standard library\", \"typing.Optional \\u2014 standard library\", \"urllib.parse.unquote \\u2014 standard library\", \"concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor, as_completed \\u2014 standard library\", \"flask.Flask, render_template, request, redirect, url_for, jsonify, Response, stream_with_context, flash \\u2014 external (Flask)\", \"markupsafe.Markup \\u2014 external (MarkupSafe)\"]\n\n### Area: web-templates\n\n**Summary:** The web-templates area provides a complete Jinja2 template suite for the Flask-based File Recovery Merger application. It uses Bootstrap 5 with a custom dark theme and implements a sophisticated UI for multi-source file recovery workflows. The templates support setup configuration, interactive file browsing with tree views, conflict resolution with side-by-side diffs, an advanced hunk-level merge editor, coverage dashboards, and real-time progress tracking via Server-Sent Events. The architecture follows template inheritance with base.html as the layout foundation, and makes heavy use of JavaScript for dynamic interactions, keyboard shortcuts, and AJAX data loading.\n\n**Cross-area references:** [\"imports Flask routes from core-application: /setup, /browse, /inventory, /conflicts, /conflict/{path}, /merge/{path}, /coverage, /log, /execute\", \"imports API endpoints from core-application: /api/browse-tree, /api/file-detail/{path}, /api/file-content/{path}, /api/coverage-files/{source}, /api/save-merge\", \"imports SSE endpoints from core-application: /scan-events, /merge-events, /extract-events\", \"imports action endpoints from core-application: /resolve, /resolve-toggle, /resolve-accept-defaults, /resolve-all-latest, /session/*, /export-log\"]\n\n**Files:**\n  - **templates/base.html** (template): Base layout template providing the common HTML structure, Bootstrap 5 dark theme, navigation bar, flash message handling, and CSS blocks for all child templates.\n    Exports: [\"base layout template with blocks: title, extra_css, content, extra_js\"]\n    Imports from: [\"Bootstrap 5.3.3 CDN (css/js)\"]\n  - **templates/setup.html** (template): Setup wizard for configuring source directories, target directory, project filters, ignore patterns, and session management with dynamic form fields.\n    Exports: [\"setup form template\"]\n    Imports from: [\"extends base.html\", \"POST /setup endpoint (core-application)\"]\n  - **templates/browse.html** (template): Interactive file browser with collapsible directory tree, version selection, conflict resolution, side-by-side diff viewing, and keyboard navigation.\n    Exports: [\"interactive file browser template\"]\n    Imports from: [\"extends base.html\", \"/api/browse-tree (core-application)\", \"/resolve, /resolve-accept-defaults (core-application)\"]\n  - **templates/inventory.html** (template): Paginated inventory table showing all files with status badges, sorting by path/size/modified date, filter tabs, and execute buttons for auto-merge and resolved files.\n    Exports: [\"paginated inventory table template\"]\n    Imports from: [\"extends base.html\", \"/execute endpoint (core-application)\"]\n  - **templates/conflicts.html** (template): Conflict resolution list showing all conflicts with status, progress bar, auto-resolve button, and navigation to individual conflict resolution pages.\n    Exports: [\"conflict list template\"]\n    Imports from: [\"extends base.html\", \"/resolve-all-latest, /execute (core-application)\"]\n  - **templates/conflict_detail.html** (template): Detailed conflict resolution page with version cards, metadata comparison, side-by-side and unified diff views, and keyboard shortcuts for rapid resolution.\n    Exports: [\"detailed conflict view template\"]\n    Imports from: [\"extends base.html\", \"/resolve, /merge/{path} (core-application)\"]\n  - **templates/merge_editor.html** (template): Advanced merge editor allowing per-hunk resolution (left/right/both/neither), visual conflict highlighting, full text edit mode, and save functionality.\n    Exports: [\"interactive merge editor template\"]\n    Imports from: [\"extends base.html\", \"/api/save-merge (core-application)\"]\n  - **templates/coverage.html** (template): Coverage dashboard showing per-source statistics with visual progress bars, breakdown by category (unique, identical, conflict selected/not selected), and expandable file lists.\n    Exports: [\"source coverage dashboard template\"]\n    Imports from: [\"extends base.html\", \"/api/coverage-files/{source} (core-application)\"]\n  - **templates/extract_history.html** (template): Setup page for extracting files from Windsurf/VS Code/Cursor editor history with detected sources, destination configuration, and project filtering.\n    Exports: [\"editor history extraction setup template\"]\n    Imports from: [\"extends base.html\", \"/extract-history endpoint (core-application)\"]\n  - **templates/extract_progress.html** (template): Real-time progress page for editor history extraction using SSE to display scanning status, file counts, copy progress, and completion statistics.\n    Exports: [\"SSE progress page for history extraction\"]\n    Imports from: [\"extends base.html\", \"/extract-events (SSE endpoint in core-application)\"]\n  - **templates/merge_progress.html** (template): Real-time merge execution progress page with SSE updates, statistics counters, and post-completion reports showing new/updated/skipped/error file lists.\n    Exports: [\"SSE progress page for merge execution\"]\n    Imports from: [\"extends base.html\", \"/merge-events (SSE endpoint in core-application)\"]\n  - **templates/scan_progress.html** (template): Real-time scanning progress page showing per-source file counts, overall progress percentage, and completion statistics with navigation to results.\n    Exports: [\"SSE progress page for file scanning\"]\n    Imports from: [\"extends base.html\", \"/scan-events (SSE endpoint in core-application)\"]\n  - **templates/log.html** (template): Action log viewer displaying merge results, file operations with status badges, recovery suggestions, and JSON export capability.\n    Exports: [\"action log viewer template\"]\n    Imports from: [\"extends base.html\", \"/export-log (core-application)\"]\n  - **templates/_file_detail.html** (template): Partial template for AJAX-loaded file details in the browse view, showing version comparison cards, diff navigation, and inline preview for single-version files.\n    Exports: [\"file detail partial template\"]\n    Imports from: [\"included by browse.html\", \"/resolve, /api/file-content, /api/file-detail (core-application)\"]\n\n### Area: agentic-knowledge\n\n**Summary:** The agentic-knowledge area contains comprehensive documentation and examples for the agentic workflow engine. It follows a self-contained documentation pattern where all five markdown files (agentic-overview, json-definitions, knowledge-system, skills, workflows) provide complete reference material without requiring source code inspection. The area uses YAML frontmatter for metadata extraction, supports progressive disclosure for knowledge injection (rules, knowledge_set, skills), and documents a layered execution model with four layer types: prompt, agentic_loop, smart_template, and tool. The example files demonstrate practical implementation of skills (folder-based SKILL.md) and workflows (JSON definitions with Jinja2 templating).\n\n**Cross-area references:** [\"references agentic.engine.run_workflow from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.engine.OpenRouterClient from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.engine.knowledge.resolve_knowledge from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.engine.knowledge.discover_skills from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.tools.definitions.json from agentic-tools\", \"references agentic.tools.read_file from agentic-tools\", \"references agentic.tools.write_file from agentic-tools\", \"references agentic.tools.list_directory from agentic-tools\", \"references agentic.tools.search_code from agentic-tools\", \"references agentic.tools.get_file_tree from agentic-tools\", \"references agentic.engine.runner.LightweightWorkflowSession from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.engine.runner.process_layer from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.engine.loop.process_agentic_loop from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.engine.loop.process_agentic_loop_native from agentic-engine\"]\n\n**Files:**\n  - **agentic/rules/docs/agentic-overview.md** (documentation): High-level architecture overview of the agentic system, serving as the entry point for understanding the framework's capabilities, directory layout, and routing to other documentation.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n  - **agentic/rules/docs/json-definitions.md** (documentation): Comprehensive documentation for creating workflows, tools, and skills via JSON definitions, covering run_workflow API, layer types (prompt, agentic_loop, smart_template, tool), and template processing with placeholders.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n  - **agentic/rules/docs/knowledge-system.md** (documentation): Documents the knowledge injection system covering three categories (rules, knowledge_set, skills), YAML frontmatter standard, and the resolution pipeline that assembles system prompts for agents.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n  - **agentic/rules/docs/skills.md** (documentation): Architecture guide for creating skills, covering folder-based SKILL.md format with YAML frontmatter, JSON skill definitions, and the discovery mechanism that makes skills available to agents.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n  - **agentic/rules/docs/workflows.md** (documentation): Workflow engine documentation describing the execution model, LightweightWorkflowSession state management, four layer types, and the full execution flow including ReAct and native tool-calling modes.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n  - **agentic/skills/example-skill/SKILL.md** (template): Example skill demonstrating the SKILL.md format with YAML frontmatter (name, description, allowed-tools) and phased instructions for directory analysis.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n  - **agentic/workflows/example_workflow.json** (config): Example workflow JSON showing a two-layer pipeline: an agentic_loop layer for file analysis using native tool-calling, followed by a smart_template layer for output formatting.\n    Exports: []\n    Imports from: []\n\n### Area: project-root-files\n\n**Summary:**              \n\n**Cross-area references:** []\n\n**Files:**\n\n\n\n## Current Area Plan\n\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"name\": \"core-application\",\n    \"description\": \"The monolithic Flask web application for multi-source file recovery and merging. Contains FileScanner, MergeEngine, EditorHistoryExtractor, SQLite session persistence, and all Flask routes in a single file.\",\n    \"file_patterns\": [\n      \"file_merger.py\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"web-templates\",\n    \"description\": \"Jinja2 HTML templates for the Flask web UI: setup wizard, file browser, inventory, conflict resolution, merge editor, coverage dashboard, and SSE progress pages. All use Bootstrap 5 dark theme.\",\n    \"file_patterns\": [\n      \"templates/*.html\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"agentic-engine\",\n    \"description\": \"Core agentic engine package: OpenRouter API client, workflow runner with multi-layer execution, ReAct-style agentic loop (text and native tool-calling modes), tool executor with safe dispatch, and knowledge/skills resolver.\",\n    \"file_patterns\": [\n      \"agentic/engine/__init__.py\",\n      \"agentic/engine/openrouter.py\",\n      \"agentic/engine/runner.py\",\n      \"agentic/engine/loop.py\",\n      \"agentic/engine/tool_executor.py\",\n      \"agentic/engine/knowledge.py\",\n      \"agentic/README.md\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"agentic-tools\",\n    \"description\": \"Tool implementations for the agentic engine: file tree walker, directory lister, file reader, code searcher, and file writer. Includes JSON tool definitions schema.\",\n    \"file_patterns\": [\n      \"agentic/tools/__init__.py\",\n      \"agentic/tools/definitions.json\",\n      \"agentic/tools/get_file_tree.py\",\n      \"agentic/tools/list_directory.py\",\n      \"agentic/tools/read_file.py\",\n      \"agentic/tools/search_code.py\",\n      \"agentic/tools/write_file.py\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"agentic-knowledge\",\n    \"description\": \"Agentic system documentation, workflow definitions, and skill examples. Rules docs cover architecture overview, JSON definitions, knowledge system, skills format, and workflow execution model.\",\n    \"file_patterns\": [\n      \"agentic/rules/docs/*.md\",\n      \"agentic/skills/example-skill/SKILL.md\",\n      \"agentic/workflows/example_workflow.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"claude-config-and-rules\",\n    \"description\": \"Claude Code configuration: global rules index, coding rules (invariants, testing, bug-fixing), skills (code-documenter, code-search), spark configuration, plans, and test infrastructure.\",\n    \"file_patterns\": [\n      \".claude/RULES_INDEX.md\",\n      \".claude/settings.local.json\",\n      \".claude/spark_config.json\",\n      \".claude/spark_plans/*.json\",\n      \".claude/spark_plans/.gitkeep\",\n      \".claude/rules/invariants.md\",\n      \".claude/rules/testing.md\",\n      \".claude/rules/bug-fixing.md\",\n      \".claude/rules/docs/.gitkeep\",\n      \".claude/skills/code-documenter/SKILL.md\",\n      \".claude/skills/code-search/SKILL.md\",\n      \".claude/tests/.gitkeep\",\n      \".claude/tests/history/.gitkeep\",\n      \".claude/spark.db\",\n      \".claude/spark.db-shm\",\n      \".claude/spark.db-wal\",\n      \".claude/spark_debug_*.log\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"project-root-files\",\n    \"description\": \"Top-level project files: CLAUDE.md project overview, PowerShell recovery script for standalone editor history extraction, commands reference, and version marker.\",\n    \"file_patterns\": [\n      \"CLAUDE.md\",\n      \"restore_deleted_files.ps1\",\n      \"commands.txt\",\n      \"0.12.0\"\n    ]\n  }\n]\n```\n\n\n## Instructions\n\nAnalyze the explorer summaries and produce a relationship map as a JSON object with `edges`, `shared_types`, `data_flows`, and `suggested_regroupings`."
