    "content": "## Repository Structure\n\n```\nGuanine(CodeEdit)/\n├── agentic/\n│   ├── engine/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   ├── knowledge.py\n│   │   ├── loop.py\n│   │   ├── openrouter.py\n│   │   ├── runner.py\n│   │   └── tool_executor.py\n│   ├── rules/\n│   │   └── docs/\n│   │       ├── agentic-overview.md\n│   │       ├── json-definitions.md\n│   │       ├── knowledge-system.md\n│   │       ├── skills.md\n│   │       └── workflows.md\n│   ├── skills/\n│   │   └── example-skill/\n│   │       └── SKILL.md\n│   ├── tools/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   ├── definitions.json\n│   │   ├── get_file_tree.py\n│   │   ├── list_directory.py\n│   │   ├── read_file.py\n│   │   ├── search_code.py\n│   │   └── write_file.py\n│   ├── workflows/\n│   │   └── example_workflow.json\n│   └── README.md\n├── sessions/\n├── templates/\n│   ├── _file_detail.html\n│   ├── base.html\n│   ├── browse.html\n│   ├── conflict_detail.html\n│   ├── conflicts.html\n│   ├── coverage.html\n│   ├── extract_history.html\n│   ├── extract_progress.html\n│   ├── inventory.html\n│   ├── log.html\n│   ├── merge_editor.html\n│   ├── merge_progress.html\n│   ├── scan_progress.html\n│   └── setup.html\n├── 0.12.0\n├── CLAUDE.md\n├── commands.txt\n├── file_merger.py\n└── restore_deleted_files.ps1\n```\n\n## Repository Metadata\n\n```json\n{\n  \"total_files\": 75,\n  \"total_lines\": 61907,\n  \"languages\": {\n    \"python\": 26,\n    \"markdown\": 14,\n    \"html\": 14,\n    \"json\": 6,\n    \"powershell\": 1\n  },\n  \"top_level_directories\": [\n    \".claude\",\n    \".code-index\",\n    \"agentic\",\n    \"templates\"\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Documentation Mode\n\nMode: **fresh**\n\n## Previous Explorer Summaries\n\n### Area: claude-config-and-rules\n\nCross-area refs: []\nSuggested splits: []\n\n### Area: agentic-tools\nThe agentic-tools area provides a suite of filesystem and code exploration utilities for the agentic engine. All tools follow a consistent pattern: they accept a `_base_dir` parameter for sandboxing, validate paths to prevent directory traversal attacks, and return JSON-encoded responses with either success data or error messages. The tools support read/write operations, directory listing (flat and recursive), file tree generation, and regex-based code search with configurable filters. The definitions.json file serves as the contract between the tool implementations and the agentic engine's tool executor, defining parameter schemas and logical tool groupings.\nCross-area refs: [\"agentic.tools.read_file.execute referenced in definitions.json\", \"agentic.tools.write_file.execute referenced in definitions.json\", \"agentic.tools.list_directory.execute referenced in definitions.json\", \"agentic.tools.search_code.execute referenced in definitions.json\", \"agentic.tools.get_file_tree.execute referenced in definitions.json\"]\nSuggested splits: []\n\n### Area: agentic-engine\nThe agentic-engine area provides a complete, framework-agnostic autonomous agent execution platform. It follows a layered architecture with clear separation: OpenRouterClient handles external LLM communication with retry logic; LightweightWorkflowSession maintains execution state across multi-layer workflows; the runner orchestrates layer dispatch (prompt, agentic_loop, smart_template, tool); loop.py implements dual-mode agentic reasoning (ReAct text-parsing and native tool-calling); tool_executor provides safe dispatch and defensive JSON parsing; and knowledge.py manages prompt assembly from markdown rules and skills. The design emphasizes stdlib-only dependencies (except Jinja2), safe execution with signature filtering, and flexible workflow definitions via JSON.\nCross-area refs: [\"imports jinja2 from external package (runner.py)\", \"references agentic.tools module in README.md examples\", \"references agentic/workflows/ directory in README.md\", \"references agentic/skills/ directory in knowledge.py discover_skills()\", \"references agentic/skill_definitions/ directory in knowledge.py discover_skills()\", \"references rules/docs/ directory in README.md documentation links\"]\nSuggested splits: []\n\n### Area: core-application\nThe core-application area is a single-file monolithic Flask web application (file_merger.py) that provides a complete file recovery and merging system. It follows an MVC architectural pattern with dataclass models (FileVersion, MergeItem, SourceConfig), service classes (FileScanner, MergeEngine, EditorHistoryExtractor, RecoveryAdvisor), and Flask route controllers. The application uses SQLite for session persistence with WAL mode for concurrent access, thread pools for parallel scanning, and Server-Sent Events for real-time progress updates. Key abstractions include the FileScanner which auto-detects and parses editor history formats (Windsurf, VS Code, Cursor) alongside regular directories, and the MergeEngine which categorizes files as unique, identical, or conflicting and executes merge operations with comprehensive logging.\nCross-area refs: [\"imports render_template from web-templates (Jinja2 templates: setup.html, scan_progress.html, inventory.html, conflicts.html, conflict_detail.html, merge_progress.html, log.html, browse.html, _file_detail.html, merge_editor.html, coverage.html, extract_history.html, extract_progress.html)\", \"references EditorHistoryExtractor.EDITOR_HISTORY_PATHS which accesses Windsurf/VS Code/Cursor history directories outside the project\", \"writes session data to local filesystem at SESSIONS_DIR (./sessions/)\", \"writes merge logs to local filesystem as merge_log_*.json files\"]\nSuggested splits: [{\"suggestion\": \"Split into modular package structure\", \"rationale\": \"The file is 2,861 lines and contains multiple distinct domains that could be separated: models (FileVersion, MergeItem, SourceConfig), services (FileScanner, MergeEngine, EditorHistoryExtractor, RecoveryAdvisor), persistence (SQLite session management), and web layer (Flask routes). Consider splitting into: models.py, scanner.py, merge_engine.py, history_extractor.py, persistence.py, and routes/ directory with route modules.\", \"priority\": \"medium\"}, {\"suggestion\": \"Extract EditorHistoryExtractor to standalone module\", \"rationale\": \"The EditorHistoryExtractor class (240+ lines) is a distinct domain dealing with editor-specific history parsing. It could be moved to a separate history_extractor.py module for better maintainability and to allow reuse by the standalone PowerShell recovery script.\", \"priority\": \"low\"}]\n\n### Area: web-templates\nThe web-templates area provides a complete Jinja2 template suite for the Flask-based File Recovery Merger application. It uses Bootstrap 5 with a custom dark theme and implements a sophisticated UI for multi-source file recovery workflows. The templates support setup configuration, interactive file browsing with tree views, conflict resolution with side-by-side diffs, an advanced hunk-level merge editor, coverage dashboards, and real-time progress tracking via Server-Sent Events. The architecture follows template inheritance with base.html as the layout foundation, and makes heavy use of JavaScript for dynamic interactions, keyboard shortcuts, and AJAX data loading.\nCross-area refs: [\"imports Flask routes from core-application: /setup, /browse, /inventory, /conflicts, /conflict/{path}, /merge/{path}, /coverage, /log, /execute\", \"imports API endpoints from core-application: /api/browse-tree, /api/file-detail/{path}, /api/file-content/{path}, /api/coverage-files/{source}, /api/save-merge\", \"imports SSE endpoints from core-application: /scan-events, /merge-events, /extract-events\", \"imports action endpoints from core-application: /resolve, /resolve-toggle, /resolve-accept-defaults, /resolve-all-latest, /session/*, /export-log\"]\nSuggested splits: []\n\n### Area: agentic-knowledge\nThe agentic-knowledge area contains comprehensive documentation and examples for the agentic workflow engine. It follows a self-contained documentation pattern where all five markdown files (agentic-overview, json-definitions, knowledge-system, skills, workflows) provide complete reference material without requiring source code inspection. The area uses YAML frontmatter for metadata extraction, supports progressive disclosure for knowledge injection (rules, knowledge_set, skills), and documents a layered execution model with four layer types: prompt, agentic_loop, smart_template, and tool. The example files demonstrate practical implementation of skills (folder-based SKILL.md) and workflows (JSON definitions with Jinja2 templating).\nCross-area refs: [\"references agentic.engine.run_workflow from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.engine.OpenRouterClient from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.engine.knowledge.resolve_knowledge from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.engine.knowledge.discover_skills from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.tools.definitions.json from agentic-tools\", \"references agentic.tools.read_file from agentic-tools\", \"references agentic.tools.write_file from agentic-tools\", \"references agentic.tools.list_directory from agentic-tools\", \"references agentic.tools.search_code from agentic-tools\", \"references agentic.tools.get_file_tree from agentic-tools\", \"references agentic.engine.runner.LightweightWorkflowSession from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.engine.runner.process_layer from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.engine.loop.process_agentic_loop from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.engine.loop.process_agentic_loop_native from agentic-engine\"]\nSuggested splits: []\n\n### Area: project-root-files\n             \nCross-area refs: []\nSuggested splits: []\n\n## Previous Relationship Map\n\n```json\n{\n  \"edges\": [\n    {\n      \"from_area\": \"core-application\",\n      \"to_area\": \"web-templates\",\n      \"type\": \"configures\",\n      \"details\": \"core-application renders Jinja2 templates via Flask render_template(): setup.html, scan_progress.html, inventory.html, conflicts.html, conflict_detail.html, merge_progress.html, log.html, browse.html, _file_detail.html, merge_editor.html, coverage.html, extract_history.html, extract_progress.html\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"from_area\": \"web-templates\",\n      \"to_area\": \"core-application\",\n      \"type\": \"calls\",\n      \"details\": \"Templates reference Flask routes and API endpoints: /setup, /browse, /inventory, /conflicts, /conflict/{path}, /merge/{path}, /coverage, /log, /execute, /api/browse-tree, /api/file-detail/{path}, /api/file-content/{path}, /api/coverage-files/{source}, /api/save-merge, /scan-events, /merge-events, /extract-events, /resolve, /resolve-toggle, /resolve-accept-defaults, /resolve-all-latest, /session/*, /export-log, /extract-history\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"from_area\": \"agentic-engine\",\n      \"to_area\": \"agentic-tools\",\n      \"type\": \"calls\",\n      \"details\": \"runner.py and loop.py dispatch tool calls via tool_executor.execute_tool_call() which invokes tool functions from the agentic.tools module (read_file, write_file, list_directory, search_code, get_file_tree); definitions.json references agentic.tools.*.execute function paths\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"from_area\": \"agentic-engine\",\n      \"to_area\": \"agentic-knowledge\",\n      \"type\": \"imports\",\n      \"details\": \"knowledge.py reads rules from agentic/rules/docs/ directory and discovers skills from agentic/skills/ and agentic/skill_definitions/ directories; runner.py calls resolve_knowledge() which loads markdown files and YAML frontmatter from the agentic-knowledge area\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"from_area\": \"agentic-knowledge\",\n      \"to_area\": \"agentic-engine\",\n      \"type\": \"shares_types\",\n      \"details\": \"Documentation references agentic.engine APIs: run_workflow, OpenRouterClient, resolve_knowledge, discover_skills, LightweightWorkflowSession, process_layer, process_agentic_loop, process_agentic_loop_native; documents layer types (prompt, agentic_loop, smart_template, tool) and execution model\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"from_area\": \"agentic-knowledge\",\n      \"to_area\": \"agentic-tools\",\n      \"type\": \"shares_types\",\n      \"details\": \"Documentation references agentic.tools.definitions.json and individual tools: read_file, write_file, list_directory, search_code, get_file_tree; documents tool parameter schemas and usage patterns\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"from_area\": \"agentic-tools\",\n      \"to_area\": \"agentic-engine\",\n      \"type\": \"configures\",\n      \"details\": \"definitions.json defines tool schemas (parameter types, descriptions) and tool_sets (code_analysis, file_ops) that the engine's tool_executor and runner consume for tool dispatch and LLM tool-calling configuration\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"from_area\": \"web-templates\",\n      \"to_area\": \"web-templates\",\n      \"type\": \"extends\",\n      \"details\": \"All page templates extend base.html for common layout, navigation, and theme; _file_detail.html is included as a partial by browse.html\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"shared_types\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Tool Definition Schema\",\n      \"defined_in\": \"agentic-tools (definitions.json)\",\n      \"used_in\": [\n        \"agentic-tools\",\n        \"agentic-engine\",\n        \"agentic-knowledge\"\n      ],\n      \"description\": \"JSON schema defining tool name, description, parameters, and execute function path. Used by tool_executor for dispatch, runner for tool registration, and documented in agentic-knowledge.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Layer Type Definitions (prompt, agentic_loop, smart_template, tool)\",\n      \"defined_in\": \"agentic-engine (runner.py)\",\n      \"used_in\": [\n        \"agentic-engine\",\n        \"agentic-knowledge\"\n      ],\n      \"description\": \"The four workflow layer types that define execution behavior. Implemented in runner.py/loop.py and extensively documented in agentic-knowledge workflows.md and json-definitions.md.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Knowledge Resolution Types (rules, skills, knowledge_set)\",\n      \"defined_in\": \"agentic-engine (knowledge.py)\",\n      \"used_in\": [\n        \"agentic-engine\",\n        \"agentic-knowledge\"\n      ],\n      \"description\": \"Three categories of knowledge injection with YAML frontmatter metadata. Implemented in knowledge.py and documented in knowledge-system.md and skills.md.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"SKILL.md Frontmatter Format\",\n      \"defined_in\": \"agentic-knowledge (skills.md documentation, example-skill/SKILL.md)\",\n      \"used_in\": [\n        \"agentic-engine\",\n        \"agentic-knowledge\"\n      ],\n      \"description\": \"YAML frontmatter schema with name, description, allowed-tools fields used by discover_skills() in knowledge.py and documented/exemplified in agentic-knowledge.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Workflow JSON Schema\",\n      \"defined_in\": \"agentic-engine (runner.py run_workflow)\",\n      \"used_in\": [\n        \"agentic-engine\",\n        \"agentic-knowledge\"\n      ],\n      \"description\": \"JSON structure for multi-layer workflow definitions with layer_def objects. Consumed by run_workflow() and documented/exemplified in agentic-knowledge (json-definitions.md, example_workflow.json).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Flask Route/Endpoint Contract\",\n      \"defined_in\": \"core-application (file_merger.py)\",\n      \"used_in\": [\n        \"core-application\",\n        \"web-templates\"\n      ],\n      \"description\": \"The set of URL routes, API endpoints, and SSE event streams that form the contract between Flask backend and Jinja2 templates. Includes /setup, /browse, /inventory, /conflicts, /execute, /api/*, /scan-events, /merge-events, /extract-events.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"FileVersion / MergeItem / SourceConfig dataclasses\",\n      \"defined_in\": \"core-application (file_merger.py)\",\n      \"used_in\": [\n        \"core-application\",\n        \"web-templates\"\n      ],\n      \"description\": \"Data models passed as template context variables to Jinja2 templates for rendering file versions, merge items, and source configurations.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"data_flows\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"File Recovery Setup and Scanning Flow\",\n      \"areas_in_order\": [\n        \"web-templates\",\n        \"core-application\",\n        \"web-templates\"\n      ],\n      \"description\": \"User submits source configuration via setup.html form -> core-application /setup route processes config and initiates FileScanner -> scan_progress.html receives SSE events from /scan-events -> inventory is built and persisted to SQLite -> user redirected to inventory.html\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Conflict Resolution Flow\",\n      \"areas_in_order\": [\n        \"web-templates\",\n        \"core-application\",\n        \"web-templates\"\n      ],\n      \"description\": \"User navigates conflicts.html -> selects a conflict -> conflict_detail.html loads version diffs from core-application -> user resolves via /resolve endpoint or opens merge_editor.html -> saves merged content via /api/save-merge -> resolution persisted to SQLite\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Merge Execution Flow\",\n      \"areas_in_order\": [\n        \"web-templates\",\n        \"core-application\",\n        \"web-templates\"\n      ],\n      \"description\": \"User triggers merge from inventory.html or conflicts.html via /execute -> core-application MergeEngine processes resolved files -> merge_progress.html receives SSE events from /merge-events -> completion stats displayed -> log.html shows results with /export-log option\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Editor History Extraction Flow\",\n      \"areas_in_order\": [\n        \"web-templates\",\n        \"core-application\",\n        \"web-templates\"\n      ],\n      \"description\": \"User configures extraction on extract_history.html -> POST /extract-history triggers EditorHistoryExtractor for Windsurf/VS Code/Cursor -> extract_progress.html receives SSE from /extract-events -> extracted files become available as sources for scanning\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Agentic Workflow Execution Flow\",\n      \"areas_in_order\": [\n        \"agentic-knowledge\",\n        \"agentic-engine\",\n        \"agentic-tools\"\n      ],\n      \"description\": \"Workflow JSON (from agentic-knowledge) loaded by run_workflow() -> runner.py iterates layers with LightweightWorkflowSession state -> knowledge.py resolves rules/skills from agentic-knowledge markdown files -> loop.py executes agentic_loop sending messages to OpenRouter API -> tool_executor dispatches tool calls to agentic-tools implementations -> results fed back into conversation loop -> final output returned through session\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Knowledge Assembly Pipeline\",\n      \"areas_in_order\": [\n        \"agentic-knowledge\",\n        \"agentic-engine\"\n      ],\n      \"description\": \"knowledge.py discover_skills() scans agentic/skills/ directories for SKILL.md files -> extract_frontmatter() parses YAML metadata -> resolve_knowledge() assembles rules from agentic/rules/docs/ markdown files + skills + knowledge_set into structured prompt content -> injected as system messages in loop.py\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"suggested_regroupings\": [\n    {\n      \"type\": \"merge\",\n      \"areas\": [\n        \"core-application\",\n        \"web-templates\"\n      ],\n      \"reason\": \"These two areas have tight bidirectional coupling: core-application renders all 13+ templates and passes data models (FileVersion, MergeItem, SourceConfig) as context, while every template references multiple Flask routes and API endpoints. They share the Flask route/endpoint contract and the data model types. The templates cannot function without the backend routes, and the backend explicitly depends on every template. They form a single cohesive web application and would be better documented as one area (e.g., 'file-merger-webapp') with sub-sections for backend logic and UI templates.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"move_files\",\n      \"areas\": [\n        \"agentic-engine\",\n        \"agentic-knowledge\"\n      ],\n      \"files_to_move\": [\n        \"agentic/README.md\"\n      ],\n      \"from_area\": \"agentic-engine\",\n      \"to_area\": \"agentic-knowledge\",\n      \"reason\": \"agentic/README.md is documentation that references agentic.tools module examples, agentic/workflows/ directory, agentic/skills/ directory, and rules/docs/ documentation links. It serves as a documentation entry point similar to the other markdown files in agentic-knowledge. Moving it would consolidate all agentic documentation in one area and keep agentic-engine focused on implementation code.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n\n## Instructions\n\nThis is iteration 2/2. Produce an area plan as a JSON object with `areas` and `rationale` keys."
