    "content": "## Repository Structure\n\n```\nGuanine(CodeEdit)/\n├── agentic/\n│   ├── engine/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   ├── knowledge.py\n│   │   ├── loop.py\n│   │   ├── openrouter.py\n│   │   ├── runner.py\n│   │   └── tool_executor.py\n│   ├── rules/\n│   │   └── docs/\n│   │       ├── agentic-overview.md\n│   │       ├── json-definitions.md\n│   │       ├── knowledge-system.md\n│   │       ├── skills.md\n│   │       └── workflows.md\n│   ├── skills/\n│   │   └── example-skill/\n│   │       └── SKILL.md\n│   ├── tools/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   ├── definitions.json\n│   │   ├── get_file_tree.py\n│   │   ├── list_directory.py\n│   │   ├── read_file.py\n│   │   ├── search_code.py\n│   │   └── write_file.py\n│   ├── workflows/\n│   │   └── example_workflow.json\n│   └── README.md\n├── sessions/\n├── templates/\n│   ├── _file_detail.html\n│   ├── base.html\n│   ├── browse.html\n│   ├── conflict_detail.html\n│   ├── conflicts.html\n│   ├── coverage.html\n│   ├── extract_history.html\n│   ├── extract_progress.html\n│   ├── inventory.html\n│   ├── log.html\n│   ├── merge_editor.html\n│   ├── merge_progress.html\n│   ├── scan_progress.html\n│   └── setup.html\n├── 0.12.0\n├── CLAUDE.md\n├── commands.txt\n├── file_merger.py\n└── restore_deleted_files.ps1\n```\n\n## Repository Metadata\n\n```json\n{\n  \"total_files\": 75,\n  \"total_lines\": 61907,\n  \"languages\": {\n    \"python\": 26,\n    \"markdown\": 14,\n    \"html\": 14,\n    \"json\": 6,\n    \"powershell\": 1\n  },\n  \"top_level_directories\": [\n    \".claude\",\n    \".code-index\",\n    \"agentic\",\n    \"templates\"\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Documentation Mode\n\nMode: **fresh**\n\n## Previous Explorer Summaries\n\n### Area: claude-config-and-rules\n\nCross-area refs: []\nSuggested splits: []\n\n### Area: agentic-tools\nThe agentic-tools area provides a suite of filesystem and code exploration utilities for the agentic engine. All tools follow a consistent pattern: they accept a `_base_dir` parameter for sandboxing, validate paths to prevent directory traversal attacks, and return JSON-encoded responses with either success data or error messages. The tools support read/write operations, directory listing (flat and recursive), file tree generation, and regex-based code search with configurable filters. The definitions.json file serves as the contract between the tool implementations and the agentic engine's tool executor, defining parameter schemas and logical tool groupings.\nCross-area refs: [\"agentic.tools.read_file.execute referenced in definitions.json\", \"agentic.tools.write_file.execute referenced in definitions.json\", \"agentic.tools.list_directory.execute referenced in definitions.json\", \"agentic.tools.search_code.execute referenced in definitions.json\", \"agentic.tools.get_file_tree.execute referenced in definitions.json\"]\nSuggested splits: []\n\n### Area: agentic-engine\nThe agentic-engine area provides a complete, framework-agnostic autonomous agent execution platform. It follows a layered architecture with clear separation: OpenRouterClient handles external LLM communication with retry logic; LightweightWorkflowSession maintains execution state across multi-layer workflows; the runner orchestrates layer dispatch (prompt, agentic_loop, smart_template, tool); loop.py implements dual-mode agentic reasoning (ReAct text-parsing and native tool-calling); tool_executor provides safe dispatch and defensive JSON parsing; and knowledge.py manages prompt assembly from markdown rules and skills. The design emphasizes stdlib-only dependencies (except Jinja2), safe execution with signature filtering, and flexible workflow definitions via JSON.\nCross-area refs: [\"imports jinja2 from external package (runner.py)\", \"references agentic.tools module in README.md examples\", \"references agentic/workflows/ directory in README.md\", \"references agentic/skills/ directory in knowledge.py discover_skills()\", \"references agentic/skill_definitions/ directory in knowledge.py discover_skills()\", \"references rules/docs/ directory in README.md documentation links\"]\nSuggested splits: []\n\n### Area: core-application\nThe core-application area is a single-file monolithic Flask web application (file_merger.py) that provides a complete file recovery and merging system. It follows an MVC architectural pattern with dataclass models (FileVersion, MergeItem, SourceConfig), service classes (FileScanner, MergeEngine, EditorHistoryExtractor, RecoveryAdvisor), and Flask route controllers. The application uses SQLite for session persistence with WAL mode for concurrent access, thread pools for parallel scanning, and Server-Sent Events for real-time progress updates. Key abstractions include the FileScanner which auto-detects and parses editor history formats (Windsurf, VS Code, Cursor) alongside regular directories, and the MergeEngine which categorizes files as unique, identical, or conflicting and executes merge operations with comprehensive logging.\nCross-area refs: [\"imports render_template from web-templates (Jinja2 templates: setup.html, scan_progress.html, inventory.html, conflicts.html, conflict_detail.html, merge_progress.html, log.html, browse.html, _file_detail.html, merge_editor.html, coverage.html, extract_history.html, extract_progress.html)\", \"references EditorHistoryExtractor.EDITOR_HISTORY_PATHS which accesses Windsurf/VS Code/Cursor history directories outside the project\", \"writes session data to local filesystem at SESSIONS_DIR (./sessions/)\", \"writes merge logs to local filesystem as merge_log_*.json files\"]\nSuggested splits: [{\"suggestion\": \"Split into modular package structure\", \"rationale\": \"The file is 2,861 lines and contains multiple distinct domains that could be separated: models (FileVersion, MergeItem, SourceConfig), services (FileScanner, MergeEngine, EditorHistoryExtractor, RecoveryAdvisor), persistence (SQLite session management), and web layer (Flask routes). Consider splitting into: models.py, scanner.py, merge_engine.py, history_extractor.py, persistence.py, and routes/ directory with route modules.\", \"priority\": \"medium\"}, {\"suggestion\": \"Extract EditorHistoryExtractor to standalone module\", \"rationale\": \"The EditorHistoryExtractor class (240+ lines) is a distinct domain dealing with editor-specific history parsing. It could be moved to a separate history_extractor.py module for better maintainability and to allow reuse by the standalone PowerShell recovery script.\", \"priority\": \"low\"}]\n\n### Area: web-templates\nThe web-templates area provides a complete Jinja2 template suite for the Flask-based File Recovery Merger application. It uses Bootstrap 5 with a custom dark theme and implements a sophisticated UI for multi-source file recovery workflows. The templates support setup configuration, interactive file browsing with tree views, conflict resolution with side-by-side diffs, an advanced hunk-level merge editor, coverage dashboards, and real-time progress tracking via Server-Sent Events. The architecture follows template inheritance with base.html as the layout foundation, and makes heavy use of JavaScript for dynamic interactions, keyboard shortcuts, and AJAX data loading.\nCross-area refs: [\"imports Flask routes from core-application: /setup, /browse, /inventory, /conflicts, /conflict/{path}, /merge/{path}, /coverage, /log, /execute\", \"imports API endpoints from core-application: /api/browse-tree, /api/file-detail/{path}, /api/file-content/{path}, /api/coverage-files/{source}, /api/save-merge\", \"imports SSE endpoints from core-application: /scan-events, /merge-events, /extract-events\", \"imports action endpoints from core-application: /resolve, /resolve-toggle, /resolve-accept-defaults, /resolve-all-latest, /session/*, /export-log\"]\nSuggested splits: []\n\n### Area: agentic-knowledge\nThe agentic-knowledge area contains comprehensive documentation and examples for the agentic workflow engine. It follows a self-contained documentation pattern where all five markdown files (agentic-overview, json-definitions, knowledge-system, skills, workflows) provide complete reference material without requiring source code inspection. The area uses YAML frontmatter for metadata extraction, supports progressive disclosure for knowledge injection (rules, knowledge_set, skills), and documents a layered execution model with four layer types: prompt, agentic_loop, smart_template, and tool. The example files demonstrate practical implementation of skills (folder-based SKILL.md) and workflows (JSON definitions with Jinja2 templating).\nCross-area refs: [\"references agentic.engine.run_workflow from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.engine.OpenRouterClient from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.engine.knowledge.resolve_knowledge from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.engine.knowledge.discover_skills from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.tools.definitions.json from agentic-tools\", \"references agentic.tools.read_file from agentic-tools\", \"references agentic.tools.write_file from agentic-tools\", \"references agentic.tools.list_directory from agentic-tools\", \"references agentic.tools.search_code from agentic-tools\", \"references agentic.tools.get_file_tree from agentic-tools\", \"references agentic.engine.runner.LightweightWorkflowSession from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.engine.runner.process_layer from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.engine.loop.process_agentic_loop from agentic-engine\", \"references agentic.engine.loop.process_agentic_loop_native from agentic-engine\"]\nSuggested splits: []\n\n### Area: project-root-files\n             \nCross-area refs: []\nSuggested splits: []\n\n## Previous Relationship Map\n\n```json\n{\n  \"edges\": [\n    {\n      \"from_area\": \"core-application\",\n      \"to_area\": \"web-templates\",\n      \"type\": \"configures\",\n      \"details\": \"core-application renders Jinja2 templates via Flask render_te