    "content": "## Your Area Assignment\n\n**Area:** agentic-tools\n**Description:** Filesystem and code exploration tool implementations for the agentic engine. Each tool follows a sandboxed execution pattern with path validation and JSON responses. Includes tool schema definitions consumed by the engine's tool executor.\n**File patterns:** [\"agentic/tools/__init__.py\", \"agentic/tools/definitions.json\", \"agentic/tools/get_file_tree.py\", \"agentic/tools/list_directory.py\", \"agentic/tools/read_file.py\", \"agentic/tools/search_code.py\", \"agentic/tools/write_file.py\"]\n\n## Plan Summary\n\nAreas in the plan:\n- agentic-engine: Core agentic workflow execution engine: LLM communication (OpenRouter), workflow runner with multi-layer dispatch, agentic loop (ReAct and native tool-calling modes), tool executor for safe dispatch, and knowledge assembly from markdown rules/skills.\n- agentic-tools: Filesystem and code exploration tool implementations for the agentic engine. Each tool follows a sandboxed execution pattern with path validation and JSON responses. Includes tool schema definitions consumed by the engine's tool executor.\n- agentic-knowledge: Documentation, rules, skills, and workflow definitions for the agentic engine. Includes the README entry point, comprehensive reference docs (overview, JSON definitions, knowledge system, skills, workflows), example skill/workflow definitions, and all markdown content consumed by knowledge.py.\n- file-merger-webapp: Monolithic Flask web application for file recovery and merging, plus all its Jinja2 templates. The backend (file_merger.py) contains data models, services (FileScanner, MergeEngine, EditorHistoryExtractor, RecoveryAdvisor), SQLite persistence, and route controllers. The templates provide a Bootstrap 5 dark-themed UI with real-time SSE progress, conflict resolution, hunk-level merge editing, and coverage dashboards. Tightly coupled bidirectionally via Flask routes, API endpoints, and template context variables.\n- claude-config: Claude Code IDE configuration: project rules (bug-fixing, invariants, testing), custom skills (code-documenter, code-search), Spark plans, settings, and test fixtures. Provides development workflow guidance and AI assistant customization.\n- project-root-files: Top-level project files: CLAUDE.md project instructions, commands reference, version marker, PowerShell recovery script, and code index artifacts.\n\n## Instructions\n\nAnalyze all files matching your area's patterns. Return a JSON report with `area`, `files`, `area_summary`, `cross_area_refs`, and optionally `suggested_splits`."
